UNIT.learningOutcomes:
By the end of the sub-strand, the learner should be able to:
a) illustrate bond types in elements, molecules and compounds;
b) investigate the relationship between bond types and physical properties of elements, molecules and compounds;
c) relate bond types and resultant structures to the uses of elements, molecules and compounds;
d) appreciate the uses of different substances based on their bond types and structures in day-to-day life.
